# Enterprise UX Constitution (Frozen)

Applies to all Catalyst One transaction workspaces. Loan Workspace is the Enterprise Reference Workspace — reuse this model; do not redesign independently.

## Workspace First

1. The workspace is always the largest and most important area of the screen.
2. Navigation, summaries, badges, and supporting chrome must never dominate.
3. Every pixel should have a purpose — avoid duplicate information, oversized headers, large unused blanks, and permanent side panels with little business value.
4. Do not overload pages; information appears only where it contributes to the current task.
5. Prefer Context Workspaces, expandable sections, tabs, and progressive disclosure over permanent cards that fill leftover space.

## Reference layout hierarchy

Workspace Header → Action Center → Primary Workspace → Context Workspace (temporary) → Timeline / Dialogue / Communication

## Action Center & Context Workspaces

1. Users never leave their current business context for routine actions.
2. Action Center in the page header is the standard entry point (frozen — do not relocate).
3. Action Center launches Context Workspaces (slide-over temporary workspaces, not CRM popups). Trailing space after removing permanent rails is reserved for these overlays.
4. Context Workspaces are dynamically composed from Enterprise Registries.
5. Communication is relationship-aware; templates are filtered by recipient, product, stage, and context.
6. Business communications enter the Enterprise Outbox before dispatch; Send Now is an intentional override.
7. Chanakya is available inside every Context Workspace.
8. Timeline, Audit Trail, and Communication History update automatically after dispatch.

## Loan / multi-lender architecture

A Loan File does **not** have a single workflow stage. Lender Pipeline is the SSOT for lender-specific statuses (login, credit, PD, legal, pricing, approval, disbursement). Do not restore a permanent “Current Stage / Sub Stage / Loan Intelligence” right panel.

## Consistency

Reuse across Opportunity, Loan, Credit Workbench, Wealth Partner, Lender, and future workspaces. Prefer `src/components/catalyst-one/action-center/` over parallel action menus.

Header rule: one Enterprise Workspace Header per screen; navigation actions belong in Action Center.
